      "pattern": null,
      "isArray": false,
      "arraySize": 1,
      "dimensions": 1,
      "description": "type -  - Determines the mathematical function used to create the blur.\n\n catmull - A spline approximation to a Gaussian kernel. Gives sharper textures and more accurate edges. gaussian - A normal distribution where pixels at the center have more effect on the resulting pixel. Gaussian lacks sharpness but handles ringing and aliasing well. box - Each pixel within the box is weighted evenly. Inexpensive and gives a \"boxy\" look. bartlette - A triangle filter. The weight of each pixel is a linear function of its distance from the center. sinc - A sharpening filter. Some pixels contribute a negative weight to the result, artifacts may occur in the form of \"ringing\". Keeps small details and edges better than Gaussian. hanning - A cosine approximation to a Gaussian kernel. blackman - A higher order cosine approximation to a Gaussian kernel.",
      "tooltip": "",
      "help": "",
      "units": "",
      "examples": [],
      "isReadOnly": false,
      "isAdvanced": false,
      "isHidden": false,
